The paper deals with image-to-image translation, specifically in the context of body pose and hand gesture translation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel GAN architecture that learns to generate new images from simple annotations, which involves conditional generation and attention mechanisms, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with the synthesis of images, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses two public datasets, indicating a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
